args:
An event called Valentine's is the talk of the
town—and the Halidom. While the prince's
friends plan something to thank him for his
tireless efforts, the question on everyone's
mind is who he will spend Valentine's with!
Excuse me, Cleo, but are you familiar\nwith an event called ＂Valentine's＂?
Ah, yes. The current topic du jour\namong people in town.
If I remember correctly, it is a time for\nmaking one's innermost feelings known\nto someone important. Why do you ask?
Well, this is merely an idea,\nbut I was thinking—
Ooo! Ooo! Are you two dishing?!\nLemme in on that sweet gossipy action!
We were just talking about Valentine's.\nAre you familiar with it, Ezelith?
Duh doy! Like I WOULDN'T be! This girl is\non the forefront of what's hot, what's not,\nand what's puuure rot.
Oh ho! And what do my ears o'erhear but\nthe cheerful chittering of lovely maidens?
Aaand here comes the empty suit.
Ah, but it is an honor to be remembered\nby a comely lass so fair.
I ALSO remember that every time you\nshow up, you start saying super-creepy\nthings like ＂comely lass.＂
Another day, another pile'a fiends slain!\nOh, hey there, folks. What's goin' on?
Was I not invited to some party?\nAlso, WHY wasn't I invited?
We were just talking about Valentine's.
Ugh. You must refer to that annual\nhappening of unparalleled jocularity.
Hold a moment. Are we discussing that\nlovely holiday that celebrates the white-\nhot passion shared between two lovers?
I am so lost right now.
Never heard of it, old man? Guess I'm\nnot surprised; it's not really much of\na holiday for geezers like you.
Yeah, I prefer to think of myself as a\ncaring big-brother type.
I am NOT calling you ＂big bro.＂\nNow then, let the genius of the group\nelucidate the particulars of this event.
Valentine's is an annual event,\nand the current talk of the town.
It is a time for sharing feelings and making\nappreciation known for people of import,\nbe they family, friend, or lover.

Many use the event to muster up their
pluck and confess a long-held, secret love.
Some even go so far as to make surprise
proffers of marriage on the spot.
Er, and some people merely use it to\nappreciate a beloved companion.
So, um...as you see, it is not wholly an\nevent which revolves around love and\nother romantic affections.
Exactly, Elisanne! And may I say, you're\nsurprisingly knowledgeable about this.
So that's Valentine's, eh? Well, wrap me\nin bacon and call me a breakfast.
I mean, we're gonna do something, yeah?\nFor {player_name}, I mean!
Well, speak of the dragon.\nHey there, {player_name}!
We were just chatting about this\nValentine's thing. You interested?
Y-Your Highness?! Gack! I, er, just\nremembered an errand I have to run!\nYes, that's it. An errand. ...Ta-ta!
But I have no errands to ru—
YOU ARE SO COMING RIGHT NOW!\nEr...farewell, everyone!
Well, they were certainly in a hurry.
Yeah, they really beat feet outta here...\nand I bet I know what they're up to!
Yo, Luca! Let's make tracks, too.
Er, where? And why? Also, now?
It's a strategy session for us men!\nC'mon, we ain't got time to waste\nstandin' around.
You didn't answer ANY of my questions!
Subtle as a pair of anvils, those two.
I only pray they're not up to some\nmanner of disruptive mischief.
Looks like this has you intrigued,\n{player_name}.
If you are so tickled by the spirit of\ncuriosity, you ought to investigate\nwhat the others are up to.
Ex-CUSE me? Why would you leave when\nyou have a perfectly good ME right here?!
Enough. You mustn't trouble him so.
Who DOES have you the most curious?\nElisanne and Cleo? Or Ranzal and Luca?
